[6] New York (Suffolk county): 1st case on Long Island, imported
Date: Wed 24 Apr 2019
Source: Long Island Press [abridged, edited]
https://www.longislandpress.com/2019/04/26/adult-case-of-measles-confirmed-in-suffolk


An adult who recently arrived from outside the USA was recently confirmed as having the 1st case of the measles on Long Island since outbreaks elsewhere in New York have been reported, officials said. The Suffolk County Department of Health Services said that the case does not appear to be related to any current measles cases in New York State, but it is jointly investigating the case with the New York State Department of Health and will take appropriate action based on the findings.

